From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 00:00:01 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Skip fake PnP AudioEndpoint for DualSense mono
 speaker.

Spider-Man Remastered needs the DualSense mono speaker MMDevice so FAudio can
open it for controller speaker effects. However, exposing that same 1-channel
controller speaker as a normal fake SWD\MMDEVAPI AudioEndpoint also makes the
game's managed audio endpoint enumeration see an extra render endpoint and
crash with an InvalidCastException at startup.

Keep creating and updating the mmdevapi render endpoint, but allow callers to
skip only the fake PnP AudioEndpoint registration. Normal audio endpoints,
DualSense haptics setup, and the non-DualSense MEDIA registration path are left
unchanged.
---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 6 +++++-
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index cb6bf9e8fb0..83c75ce58f3 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -802,7 +802,11 @@ static void MMDevice_Register(const WCHAR *instguid, const WCHAR *friendly_name,
     {
         WCHAR device_name[DEVICE_ID_LEN];
 
-        if (swprintf(device_name, ARRAY_SIZE(device_name), L"SWD\\MMDEVAPI\\{0.0.%u.00000000}.%s", flow, instguid) != -1)
+        if (skip_audioendpoint)
+        {
+            TRACE("Skipping fake PnP AudioEndpoint registration for %s.\n", debugstr_w(friendly_name));
+        }
+        else if (swprintf(device_name, ARRAY_SIZE(device_name), L"SWD\\MMDEVAPI\\{0.0.%u.00000000}.%s", flow, instguid) != -1)
         {
             memset(&device_info_data, 0, sizeof(device_info_data));
             device_info_data.cbSize = sizeof(device_info_data);
-- 
